                          <strong>Job title:</strong> Forward Deployed Engi=
neer, GenAI, Google Cloud - Bengaluru, Mumbai or=20
Gurugram <br>
<strong>Job description:</strong> As an AI Forward Deployed Engineer (FDE) =
at Google Cloud, you are an=20
embedded builder who bridges the gap between frontier AI products and=20
production-grade reality within customers. Unlike traditional advisory=20
roles, you function as a &quot;builder-consultant,&quot; moving beyond high=
-level=20
architecture to code, debug, and jointly ship bespoke agentic solutions=20
directly within the customer=E2=80=99s environment. You will manage blocker=
 to=20
production including solving the integration complexities, data readiness=
=20
issues, and state-management challenges that prevent AI from reaching=20
enterprise-grade maturity. By embedding with strategic accounts, you serve=
=20
a dual purpose: providing &quot;white glove&quot; deployment of complex AI =
systems=20
and acting as a critical feedback loop, transforming real-world field=20
insights into Google Cloud=E2=80=99s future product roadmap. <br><br>
  <strong>Minimum qualifications:</strong>=20
  <ul>
      <li>Bachelor&#39;s degree in Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathem=
atics, or=20
equivalent practical experience.</li>
      <li>3 years of experience in Python and relevant machine learning pac=
kages=20
(e.g., keras, HF transformers).</li>
      <li>Experience in applied AI, with a focus on building systems around=
=20
pretrained models (e.g., prompt engineering, fine-tuning,=20
Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), orchestrating model interactions with=
=20
external tools to deliver solutions).</li>
      <li>Experience implementing multi-agent systems using frameworks (e.g=
.,=20
LangGraph, CrewAI, etc.) and patterns like ReAct, self-reflection, and=20
hierarchical delegation.</li>
  </ul>
  <strong>Preferred qualifications:</strong>
  <ul>
      <li>Master&#39;s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a relate=
d technical=20
field.</li>
      <li>Experience training and fine tuning models in large scale environ=
ments=20
(e.g., image, language, recommendation) with accelerators.</li>
      <li>Experience in systems design with the ability to architect and ex=
plain data=20
pipelines, ML pipelines, and ML training and serving approaches.</li>
      <li>Experience working with customers in a technical capacity.</li>
      <li>Knowledge of &quot;LLM-native&quot; metrics (tokens/sec, cost-per=
-request) and=20
techniques for optimizing state management and granular tracing.</li>
      <li>Ability to be action-oriented, with a focus on solving customer p=
roblems.</li>
  </ul>
  <strong>Job responsibilities:</strong>=20
  <ul>
      <li>Serve as the lead developer for complex AI applications, transiti=
oning from=20
rapid prototypes to production-grade agentic workflows (e.g., multi-agent=
=20
systems, MCP servers) that drive measurable return on investment.</li>
      <li>Architect and code the &quot;connective tissue&quot; between Goog=
le=E2=80=99s AI products and=20
customer&#39;s live infrastructure, including APIs, legacy data silos, and=
=20
security perimeters.</li>
      <li>Build high-performance evaluation (Eval) pipelines and observabil=
ity=20
frameworks to ensure agentic systems meet requirements for accuracy,=20
safety, and latency.</li>
      <li>Identify repeatable field patterns and technical &quot;friction p=
oints&quot; in=20
Google=E2=80=99s AI stack, converting them into reusable modules or formal =
product=20
feature requests for the Engineering teams.</li>
      <li>Co-build with customer engineering teams to instill Google-grade=
=20
development best practices, ensuring long-term project success and high=20
end-user adoption.</li>
  </ul>
</td>
